[Name] PowerTOP
[Summary] Power consumption measurement and estimation tool
[Description] Computer programs can make your computer use more power.
PowerTOP is a Linux tool that helps you find those programs that are
misbehaving while your computer is idle. PowerTOP combines various sources of
information from the kernel into one screen so that you can see how well your
system is doing at saving power, and which components are the biggest
problems. 
